('b00003', 'Lost In The Jungle', 'img_book/3.png', 42000, 1000, 1, 1, 1, 'Just imagine a northern Vietnamese teen-age soldier and an American soldier&nbsp;imprisoned in a jungle cave by an ethnic tribe and forced to eat frogs and rats&nbsp;roasted by an open ire and you are immediately drawn into what can only be&nbsp;described as a very special if not unique story.\nThis gripping and humane tale has been awarded a prize by the Vietnamese&nbsp;Association of Writers and another prestigious prize by the Ministry of Defense.\n', '', 'Lost in the Jungle&nbsp;has won a prestigious State Prize in Vietnam, one of two&nbsp;which its author Trung Trung Dinh has been awarded over the years. For readers&nbsp;this may constitute an appealing, but, on the other hand dubious, distinction. At a&nbsp;minimum we know there is recognition that the story is well told and has cultural,&nbsp;historical or social value. \n'),
